# Machine profile: 2x AMD Radeon AI PRO R9700 (gfx1201, RDNA4, ~31 GiB VRAM each)
#
# profiles/r9700-dual/default.env -- card-generic defaults for spanning ONE model
# across BOTH discrete R9700s (weights that don't fit a single 31 GiB card live in
# VRAM across the pair, no CPU-MoE offload). Sourced by run-vulkan.sh for every
# model run with MACHINE=r9700-dual.
#
# Split of responsibility (see the launcher header for resolution order):
#   - This file:                       what's true for ANY model on this GPU pair
#                                      (multi-GPU split, threads/batch, mmap policy).
#   - profiles/r9700-dual/<model>.env: per-model VRAM-fit tuning (ctx, ubatch, KV
#                                      quant) that depends on that model's weights.
#   - models/<model>.env:              model-intrinsic settings (path, sampling).
# Every value is a shell default (`:=`, only applied if unset), so a per-model
# profile or the CLI can override it.
#
# This host (Turin server board) exposes NO iGPU: both PCI VGA devices ARE the
# R9700s, so Vulkan enumerates exactly two devices and there is nothing to hide.
# We therefore leave GPU_INDEX UNSET on purpose -- run-vulkan.sh only injects
# GGML_VK_VISIBLE_DEVICES when GPU_INDEX is non-empty, so leaving it unset keeps
# BOTH cards visible to RADV. (If a future host adds an iGPU, set
# GGML_VK_VISIBLE_DEVICES explicitly to the two discrete indices instead.)
#
# Notes for this card:
#   - gfx1201 is natively supported on modern ROCm (>= 7.x). Vulkan/RADV ignores
#     ROCm-only knobs (GFX/UMA/*_VISIBLE_DEVICES), so those are left unset here.
#   - Dedicated VRAM (not unified), so UMA env vars are intentionally unset.

: "${ENABLE_UMA:=0}"                        # dedicated VRAM, no unified-memory hack

# --- multi-GPU split ---------------------------------------------------------
# llama.cpp splits a model across GPUs via --split-mode + --tensor-split.
#   layer mode: whole layers are assigned to each GPU (low inter-GPU traffic,
#               best for a 2-card PCIe box). tensor-split gives the per-GPU
#               weighting; "1,1" = even. Nudge toward the card that is NOT also
#               driving a display if you see one card OOM before the other.
SPLIT_MODE="${SPLIT_MODE:-layer}"
TENSOR_SPLIT="${TENSOR_SPLIT:-1,1}"
LLAMA_ARGS+=(--split-mode "${SPLIT_MODE}" --tensor-split "${TENSOR_SPLIT}")

# Card-generic baselines. Per-model profiles override CTX_SIZE/UBATCH to fit a
# given model's weights; these are just sane fallbacks for a model without one.
: "${CTX_SIZE:=32768}"
: "${UBATCH:=1024}"
: "${BATCH:=8192}"
: "${THREADS:=8}"

# Keep mmap ON (do NOT pass --no-mmap): rootless podman caps memlock at the
# systemd user limit (often 8 MiB), so --no-mmap would try to lock the whole
# model in host RAM and fail. mmap-ing the GGUF from the read-only mount
# sidesteps the memlock ceiling. See profiles/r9700/default.env for the rationale.
: "${NO_MMAP:=0}"
